A good tip in big business is that if you ever find yourself sending an uns=
olicited nine-figure=C2=A0bid for something, you should end your bid letter=
 by saying =E2=80=9CAnd yes, this is totally legit.=E2=80=9D If you do not =
end that way, the person receiving your unsolicited nine-figure bid letter =
might wonder if it is in fact legit; they might conclude that it is not, an=
d throw the letter away instead of calling you to negotiate. Whereas =E2=80=
=9Cthis is totally legit=E2=80=9D conveys the important information that it=
 is totally legit. I used to be a mergers and acquisitions lawyer and =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0no, I=E2=80=99m sorry, I=E2=80=99m kidding here,=C2=A0in high-s=
takes M&A auctions I cannot recall ever receiving a bid package ending =E2=
=80=9Cthis is totally legit.=E2=80=9D Context clues allowed me to conclude =
that bid packages were totally legit. If you end a=C2=A0bid =E2=80=9CAnd ye=
s, this is totally legit,=E2=80=9D it=E2=80=99s because you know the contex=
t clues are not helping.Anyway here=E2=80=99s a letter that Rumble Inc.=C2=
=A0wrote to podcaster Joe Rogan and posted on Twitter yesterday, saying in =
part:How about you bring all your shows to Rumble, both old and new, with n=
o censorship, for 100 million bucks over four years?This is our chance to s=
ave the world. And yes, this is totally legit.I am not sure how serious it =
actually is:The offer, made public in a letter from Rumble Chief Executive =
Chris Pavlovski posted to Twitter, follows Spotify CEO Daniel Ek=E2=80=99s =
letter to employees on Sunday apologizing for Mr. Rogan=E2=80=99s use of a =
racial slur in previous podcast episodes and saying he doesn=E2=80=99t beli=
eve in =E2=80=9Csilencing=E2=80=9D him. Spotify has said Mr. Rogan signed a=
 multiyear deal with the company in September 2020. It is unclear whether M=
r. Rogan would be able to switch platforms any time soon. =E2=80=A6Mr. Ek s=
aid in his letter that Mr. Rogan chose to remove some episodes from Spotify=
 after discussions with the company and Mr. Rogan=E2=80=99s own reflections=
. Tracking site jremissing.com says 113 of Mr. Rogan=E2=80=99s episodes hav=
e been taken off Spotify since Friday.But Rumble also has signed a deal to =
merge with a SPAC called CF Acquisition Corp. VI, and the stock was up 18% =
yesterday. Just offering Joe Rogan $100 million added some $500 million to =
Rumble=E2=80=99s market value.[6] I suppose you can tell a story about this=
 letter increasing Rumble=E2=80=99s expected future cash flows by $500 mill=
ion, but I won=E2=80=99t. My advice to CEOs recently has been pretty much =
=E2=80=9Cdo meme stuff,=E2=80=9D and if you are a right-wing media SPAC in =
2022 surely the meme-iest thing you can do is say =E2=80=9CJoe Rogan=E2=80=
=9D a lot. So, makes sense.=C2=A0They should offer him $200 million to host=
=C2=A0just=C2=A0the shows that use racial slurs.
