=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What if you tried to separate =
out that rare coolness from the shoes? What if you, like, advertised that y=
ou would let people take pictures with your rare Nikes to post on social me=
dia? I am not an intellectual property lawyer but I feel like eventually Ni=
ke Inc. would get annoyed. You own the=C2=A0<em>shoes</em>, sure, but Nike =
owns the intellectual property. You can resell the shoes, but the brand bel=
ongs to Nike.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/26639604.260613/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnR=
