g the same pair of sneakers for $500=C2=A0<em>and keeping the shoes</em>,[7=
]</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">there is really only one logical ch=
oice. The problem is, why should Nike let <em>you </em>do this? Why shouldn=
=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>Nike=C2=A0</em>do this? Nike, as the issuer of Nikes, s=
hould be the one selling rare Nikes and not delivering them. That makes the=
m especially rare! It=E2=80=99s one thing for StockX to sell you an Air Jor=
dan 4 and hang onto it, but Nike can sell you an Air Jordan 69,420 and not =
even make it! It=E2=80=99s the rarest sneaker of all! Exactly zero were eve=
r made![8] It=E2=80=99s worth millions.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D=
